	   <tr><td colspan=2>As far as statwise on your str, agi, dex the dwarf is the best paladin in the game by far. I myself picked a human..why because I like a challenge and go against the grain. I will say this never NEVER use flash of light on a mob, unless you root it first or already in the middle of battle. Its used best when fighting player vs player. I will say this after lvl 24 or so.. head to Lake of ill omen..much better xp, not so great loot on most mobs..except sarnaks there good loot is rare, but its worth it. After lvl 30ish go to Fronier mountains and fight giants.. they give out some decent loot, but not so good xp so you will be there awhile or head to the Overthere, fantastic xp til after lvl 40. I will say this much once you hit about lvl 35 you can pretty much say you will be in Karnak for the rest of your characters lvls. Its really the only place to be for xp. If its coin your after get with a group of folks once you hit in your 30's and fight Hill Giants they usually drop anywhere from 5 to 30pp at a time.. but occasionally they drop gold. I find the Rathe Mountains to be the best hunting ground for them. Then you can start affording your good weapons. Also in your 30s dont forget about your quests either..some dont think the Ro armor is worth going after..but believe me its important. Xp is good, as well as much needed faction building for all Paladin factions..especially the Deepwater Paladins (for those who dont know who they are They are the Erudite Paladins), you will need to get to Ally in order to do your epic for the Fiery Avenger. So dont throw away what little Verant might give us. Then eventually go after your deepwater armor and then get your skyshine armor at super uber lvls. Once you make lvl 45 also start going on the Dragon raids (Naggy and Vox) they each drop the half of the book needed for the epic. <br>Thats the reason most of us Paladins lvl slower than other classes.. we have lots of quests in our long journey..but it does pay off later. :) If you have any questions feel free to post here or you can e-mail me at tsalathe@juno.com<br>May the Power of Rocent Nife bless you all in your endeavors.<br><br>Aamadanae Whirlwind<br>45th Paladin of The Knights of Burning Justice<br>and War Council member of The Phoenix Legion<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
