	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 16th 1:37 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sounds like a pretty suckbag situation.  Here's my advice (and this will work for any char above lvl 7 or so).<br><br>Go to Befallen.  There's a strategy I used here to build a good amount of cash in a relatively short amount of time.  The first thing is to spend a few hours killing orcs in West Commons to build faction with the local merchants.  After that, solo into befallen and hang out in the main room at the top of the stairs.  Don't fight anything unless attacked.  <br><br>Here's the trick:  Say another PC kills a scarred initiate that is wearing an apprentice robe.  You can only have one of these robes in your possesion at a time.  So after the PC kills the initiate, he will likely not be able to loot the robe because he already has one.  You wait till the no-loot timeout expires then loot it.  Then take it to the inn over the hill (*not* the hut right in front of befallen) and sell it to the merchant.  If you have good faction you will get 2p2g for the robe.  Go back into befallen and repeat.  <br><br>Using this method I have literally made 100p in four hours and gained no exp!  :-)  There were times when I only needed to run in and grab a robe and leave without waiting at all!  If you kill an apprentice with a cracked staff, that adds another 1.5p.  Occasionally, higher level players will also not loot the cracked staves.  Essentially, you're picking plat up off the floor.<br><br>A few notes, though: First, despite that other players don't loot the robes, expect to be accused of ninja looting now and again.  Be ready to explain yourself.  I find the best way to do this is by asking them why they aren't looting the robes.  Of course, the response will be that they already have one and can't continue to loot them.  Then ask them what the problem is...<br><br>Second, expect to die a few times.  Either you'll run into a nasty train that roots you or you'll have a run in with Dragoon Zytl or Gix while you're cashing in robes.  Such is life.<br><br>Lastly, 2p2g isn't exactly a truckload of cash but the key is that you sell to merchants, not other PCs.  You're not sitting around for hours at a time auctioning and haggling to make a buck.  <br><br>Have fun!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
