	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Fellow Dwarven Paladin!<br><br>I would recommend starting to look into Fine Steel Plate.  It usually goes for about 10 plat per AC pt, maybe less for some pieces.  You can pick up a fine steel face plat for less than 50 plat, even though it is AC 7.  The fine steel will serve you well for many levels to come. And if you know someone that is a smith, you can even get dyed FS Plate that looks pretty sharp!<br><br>Once you reach level 30-35 you can start looking into the Ro Armor quests if you are interested.<br><br>Ry'Gorr is another good choice, but it can be pricey for certain pieces. If you have the cash though at level 23, this would be a good option.<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>49th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
